      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL SAKI (3) was an effortless winner last time as she ran right away with a 6 length win at this track (23.54). Great chance to get the job done again. DEARDEN (2) had been in great form but missed the frame latest when eighth (24.92) in a Grade 4 at this track. Normally safe to begin but shuffled back last time off the low draw. Form here at the trip excellent including two wins. One of the main contenders. GEORGE ALEXIS (4) tends to drift back and work into the race, charging home into the minors two back before winding up late into third (23.92) in a Grade 4 at this track last time. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Leading player again. BEST EDITION (1) won by a wide margin last start. Sure to run well again.",
